World Bank Finances Higher Education in Hungary
WASHINGTON , February 26 ( Xinhua ) -- The World Bank approved Thursday a loan of 150 million U.S. dollars equivalent for higher education project in Hungary to support its comprehensive reform program for higher education .
The project is designed to develop a system of higher education that responds to the nation 's changed and changing social and economic needs , operates efficiently and mobilizes greater private finance and distributes the costs of education more fairly .
Since Hungary joined the World Bank in 1982 , the Bank commitments total some 4.35 billion dollars for 40 projects .
